The paper deals with machine learning and specifically focuses on domain generalization for object recognition. The proposed method involves training a feature extractor over a diverse set of domains and enforcing pair-wise domain invariance through an adversarial approach. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the problem addressed in the paper.
